    About

    Description

    The cat, commonly referred to as the domestic cat or house cat, is a small domesticated carnivorous mammal. It is the only domesticed species in the family Felidae. Recent advances in archaeology and genetics have shown that the domestication of the cat occurred in the Near East around 7500 BC. Wikipedia
    Lifespan : 12 18years (Domesticated)
    Scientific name : Felis catus
    Gestation period : 65days
    Class : Mammalia
    Domain : Eukaryota
    Family : Felidae
